#[doc("""
Minimal four-level logging over the `Log` effect: `log.debug`,
`log.info`, `log.warn`, `log.error`, each `Unit / Log`.

The runtime ships a default `Log` handler, installed when `main`'s
row mentions `Log`, that writes each call to stderr in
`[YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ] LEVEL message` form (ISO 8601 UTC
timestamp, 5-char left-padded level, message, newline) and flushes
after every line. Install a custom `Log` handler to capture output
without touching stderr.

The default handler does not filter by level — all four levels
write unconditionally — and messages are plain `String`s.
""")]

# ---- public surface ----

#[doc("Logs `msg` at the debug level (rides `Log`).")]
pub fn debug(msg: String) : Unit / Log = Log.debug(msg)

#[doc("Logs `msg` at the info level (rides `Log`).")]
pub fn info(msg: String) : Unit / Log = Log.info(msg)

#[doc("Logs `msg` at the warning level (rides `Log`).")]
pub fn warn(msg: String) : Unit / Log = Log.warn(msg)

#[doc("Logs `msg` at the error level (rides `Log`).")]
pub fn error(msg: String) : Unit / Log = Log.error(msg)
